				<p><p>Using PID control in Line Follower of course require you to define the Error value for every condition of sensors, treat empty line just like straight line: which is 0 error. You should provide more info about your sensor setup, though it is better to have many sensors aligned in the front of the robot.</p>

<p>following is simple illustration example of the error look-up table based on sensors reading if you have 8 sensors, bit 1 represents reading of black Line:</p>

<pre><code>sensor   : error
11000000 :-3
01100000 :-2
00110000 :-1
00011000 : 0
00000000 : 0 # line gap
00001100 :+1
00000110 :+2
00000011 :+3
</code></pre>

<p>with 0 error, PID calculation should result in straight forward move</p>
